# Analysis of the Main Target Image

## Count & Layers
I can see two distinct structures in the main target image:

1. **Main Tower Structure** (right side):
   - Total blocks: 10 blocks
   - Layers: 5 layers from bottom to top

2. **Small Vehicle Structure** (left side):
   - Total blocks: 4 blocks
   - Layers: 3 layers

## Spatial Relationships

### Tower Structure (bottom to top):
- Layer 1: Yellow horizontal rectangular base block
- Layer 2: Red square block with a circular hole/tunnel through it
- Layer 3: Yellow horizontal rectangular block
- Layer 4: Two green vertical rectangular pillars side by side with space between them
- Layer 5: Yellow horizontal rectangular block on top
- Top: Orange triangular prism (roof) positioned on the right side of the top block

### Vehicle Structure:
- Bottom: Two yellow half-cylindrical blocks (wheels)
- Middle: Yellow horizontal rectangular block
- Top: Orange triangular prism (roof) positioned on the right side

# Required Blocks from Dictionary

## For Tower Structure:
- 3× Block #11 (yellow horizontal rectangular blocks)
- 1× Block #1 (red arch block - front left of tunnel)
- 1× Block #2 (red arch block - front right of tunnel)
- 1× Block #3 (red arch block - back left of tunnel)
- 1× Block #4 (red arch block - back right of tunnel)
- 1× Block #7 (green vertical rectangular block)
- 1× Block #8 (green vertical rectangular block)
- 1× Block #15 (orange triangular prism)

## For Vehicle Structure:
- 1× Block #11 (yellow horizontal rectangular block)
- 2× Block #12 (yellow half-cylindrical blocks for wheels)
- 1× Block #15 (orange triangular prism)
